The paper deals with Vision-to-Language (V2L) problems, which involve computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a method of incorporating high-level concepts into the CNN-RNN approach, which is a common technique in natural language processing, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of external semantic information, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper provides an analysis of the value of high-level semantic information, which could be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
